extends ../../docs-template-partials/_docs-article

block prepend article
  - var sectionId = "getting-started-codebase-html-generator-mixins"
  - var sectionTitle = "Codebase HTML Generator Mixins"

block section
  p.
    Codebase has some handy Pug HTML generator mixins. These have been used in  generating some of the docs and #[a(href="examples.html") examples], and you can also use them for rapid prototyping.
  
  p.
    Following these example HTML generators, you can also generate your own. Examples of others in the the Codebase project can be found in the #[code .popover--fix] example (a popover with a lot of tabular content), and in the example blog index excerpts loop.
    
  h3 "Lorem ipsum" Paragraph Generator
  
  p.
    When this paragraph mixin is included, it will generate up to four paragraphs in your HTML depending on how many you specify. You can also add some classes to the first paragraph (e.g. if you require it to have a dropcap, or enlarged "lead" text, or some #[a(href="decoration.html") decoration] classes).
  
  p.
    See #[a(href="codebase/pug/generators/_paragraphs.pug") codebase/pug/generators/_paragraphs.pug].
  
  pre
    code.
      mixin paragraph(number, p1Class)
        case number
          when 1
            p(class=p1Class).
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet ...
          when 2
            p(class=p1Class).
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet ...
            p.
              Summo nostro dicunt sea ut ...
          when 3
            p(class=p1Class).
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet ...
            p.
              Summo nostro dicunt sea ut ...
            p.
              Utroque habemus moderatius cum cu ...
          when 4
            p(class=p1Class).
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet ...
            p.
              Summo nostro dicunt sea ut ...
            p.
              Utroque habemus moderatius cum cu ...
            p.
              Eruditi omittam usu et ...
          default
            Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet ...
  
  p.
    (In the actual mixin these paragraphs are written in full.)
    
  p Usage:
  
  pre
    code.
      //- To get one paragraph (default):
      
      +paragraph
      
      //- To get a specific number of paragraphs (up to 4)

      +paragraph(2)
      
      //- To add some classes to the first paragraph
      
      +paragraph(1, "b--heavy")
      
      +paragraph(3, "lead text--purple")
  
  
  h3 Menu and Menubar Generators
  
  p.
    Mixins for rapid generation of menus and menubars have been provided.
    
  p.
    See #[a(href="codebase/pug/generators/_menus.pug") codebase/pug/generators/_menus.pug].
    
  pre
    code.
      //- Menu generator

      mixin menu(menuLink, total, menuClass)
        - var n = 0;
        ul(class=["menu", menuClass])
          while n < total
            li
              a(href="#/")= menuLink
                = " "
                = (n++ + 1)

      //- Menubar generator

      mixin menubar(menuLink, total, menuClass)
        - var n = 0;
        ul(class=["menubar", menuClass])
          while n < total
            li
              a(href="#/")= menuLink
                = " "
                = (n++ + 1)

  p.
    Usage: in the parameters specify:
    
  ol
    li The text of the menu link
    li The number of menu items
    li Any classes you require to be added (optional)
      
  p.
    Examples:
    
  pre
    code.
      //- a 5-item menu:
      
      +menu("Menu link", 5)
      
      //- a 4-item menubar, centered
      
      +menubar("Test", 4, "menubar--center")
  
  h3 Table Generator
  
  p.
    This mixin builds a demo table for you.
    
  p.
    See #[a(href="codebase/pug/generators/_tables.pug") codebase/pug/generators/_tables.pug].
  
  pre
    code.
      mixin table(totalColumns, totalRows, tableClass)
        table(class=["table", tableClass])
          thead
            tr
              - for (var cols = 0; cols < totalColumns; cols++)
                th= "Table Header"
                  = " "
                  = (cols + 1)
          tbody
            - for (var rows = 0; rows < totalRows; rows++)
              tr
                - for (var cols = 0; cols < totalColumns; cols++)
                  td= "Table content"
                    = " "
                    = (cols + 1)
                    = "."
                    = (rows + 1)

  p.
    Usage: in the parameters specify:
    
  ol
    li The number of rows
    li The number of columns
    li Any classes you require to be added (optional)
      
  p.
    Examples:
  
  pre
    code.
      +table(3, 4)
      
      +table(6, 5, "bg--yellow")
